OCKER           Country bumpkin or someone ignorant (Also refer's to
                'blue collar' workers, with a particular strain of accent)

ONYA            Goodonya, well done

{
OPAL            Unique Australian Gem Stone - has every colour of the
                rainbow and is only obtained through lots of hard work!
}

OPTY            Optometrist

O.T.            Over the top.

OTHER SIDE OF THE BLACK STUMP
                Way outback, even further than never never or back of beyond

OUTBACK         The bush or the wilderness

OWERYAGOINGMATORRIGHT?
                How are you?
                 {Literal Translation - How are you going, mate? All right?}

PASH            Deep kiss, similar to French kiss

PLURRY          Alternative to 'bloody'

POINT THE BONE AT, TO
                To blame

POM             British person (also Pommy)

PRANG           An accident; also (vb.) to have an accident: "I pranged
                the car, and it was a write-off"

PRAWN           Shrimp

QUAKY ISLES     New Zealand

RAPT            Very happy with; "He's rapt!"

RAW PRAWN, TO COME THE
                To try to deceive someone

RAZOO OR BRASS RAZOO
                An Australian coin; also an expression of ignorance
                "he couldn't give a brass razoo about it"

RIGHT?, ARE YOU RIGHT?
                "Are you ready to go?"; also "Have you hurt
                yourself?"; also "Is everything all right?"

RIPPER          Something really good

ROO             Kangaroo

RUBBER          Eraser

RUBBISH BIN     Garbage can, usually small

RUG UP          To keep warm, to protect against cold weather

RUM             No good

SANDGROPER      West Australian

SCHOONER        Size of beer glass, larger than a midi.

SHE'S COOL      Everything is fine; everything is alright

SHEILA          A woman

SHOOT THROUGH   To leave quickly

SHOUT           To buy something for someone, usually a drink

SILK SHIRT ON A PIG
                A waste or something useless

SNAG            Sausage

SPACK           To go crazy

SQUATTER        Someone who occupies owned land illegally

STATION         Large farm or ranch

STREWTH!        All purpose abbreviation for "it's the truth"; also 
                expression of surprise

STRIFE          Trouble

STROPPY         Cantankerous

STUBBIE         Glass bottle,  small glass beer bottle, usually w/short
                neck

SUNBURNT COUNTRY, THE
                Australia

SUNDOWNER       Wanderer or tramp

SWAG            Bedroll and all the worldly goods of the swagman

SWAGMAN         Vagabond, tramp

TA              Thankyou

TALL POPPY      Someone 'above the crowd', cut down to size (Tall
                Poppy Syndrome)

TASSIE          Tasmania

TASWEGIAN       A person from Tasmania (Also Tasmanian)

TA-TA           Goodbye

TELLY           Television

TERRITORIAN     One from the Northern Territory

TEXTA           Colour marker pen

TIC             A moment, a second: "be back in a tic"

TIN or TINNY    Can, usually the Amber Fluid

TINNY           Dubious (in sense of danger, chance of failure), iffy
                (activity, enterprise)

TOO RIGHT       No kidding, you bet [archaic]

TRANNIE         Portable radio

TROPPO          Mad or insane, due to subtropical exposure

TRUE BLUE DINKI DI
                Unmistakably Australian

TUCKER          Food

TYKE            Dog

UP A GUMTREE    State of confusion

UTE             Tray-type car; called pickup in the US

WAFFLE          To talk endlessly about nothing...to 'waffle on'

WALKABOUT       To take a hike in the outback, sometimes for a very long
                time

WANKER          Drone, idle and unnecessary person (from vb. "to wank")
                (very impolite ){suggests possible blindness later in life}

WEAGLE          A player/supporter of the West Coast Eagles football team

WESTRALIA       Western Australia

WESTRALIAN      Someone from Western Australia

WHACK, TO GET A To get a fair share

WHINGE          To complain

WILLY WILLY     Natural whirlwind or dust twister

WINDIES         The West Indian cricket team

WOBBLY, TO CHUCK A
                To get annoyed or angry

WONKY           Broken, bent, out of place

WOOP WOOP       Imaginary place which is a byword for backwardness
                and remote-ness, eg "he comes from woop woop."

WOWSER          Self-righteous censor

WRITE-OFF       (state of) a car that cannot be repaired (see "prang")

WURLEY          An aboriginal temporary shelter

YABBER          To talk

YABBY/YABBIE    Freshwater crayfish

YAKKA           Work

YANK            American (sometimes applied to Canadians)

YARRA           Insane, {also name of Melbourne's river - the only river
                 in the world that flows up-side down.}

YOBBO           Idiot; Larrakin

YONKS           A long time; "Haven't seen you in yonks"

ZAC             (archaic) sixpence - predecimal currency

